A HAVERSACK, some barley-meal, a eloak, a stick, a cup—these were the Cynie’s scanty furniture; but now he thinks this over much. For, seeing a bumpkin drink from his hollowed hands, quoth he: “ Why do I carry you about, you useless cup? ”
